</p>
      <p>where the latent variable <italic>I</italic>
<sub><italic>in</italic></sub> denotes read identity, i.e., where the isoform read <italic>n</italic> in cell <italic>i</italic> came from. For bulk RNA-seq methods like MISO [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR8">8</xref>] and DICEseq [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR9">9</xref>], the conditional distribution of the read identity <italic>I</italic>
